This paper deals with probabilistic query evaluation over probabilistic graphs, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.DB (databases), as the paper focuses on tuple-independent probabilistic databases. Additionally, the paper deals with ontology-mediated queries, which are often studied in the context of knowledge representation and reasoning, falling under cs.AI (artificial intelligence). The paper also uses graph-theoretic concepts and reductions, which are common in cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CC (computational complexity). Finally, the paper uses probabilistic models and techniques, which are studied in cs.LG (machine learning) and other related sub-fields.
